Evaluate diet and spatial overlap

Max Lindmark

29 November, 2022

Intro

In this script, I take the collated stomach data set and calculate aggregates (feeding ratio, total weight of prey groups) and predictor variables for diet data, aggregate to get 1 stomach = 1 row per prey type (not prey individual). I also select only the columns I need for model fitting, join environmental covariates and cpue covariates for cod and flounder, and lastly saduria biomass densities.

Read stomach data

stom <- read_csv("data/clean/clean_stomach_data_all_prey.csv") %>% as.data.frame()
#> Rows: 88335 Columns: 24
#>  Column specification 
#> Delimiter: ","
#> chr  (8): pred_id, predator_latin_name, species, ices_rect, haul_id, pred_we...
#> dbl (16): pred_weight_g, pred_length_cm, year, quarter, month, day, subdiv, ...
#> 
#>  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
#>  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.

wide_cod <- stom %>% 
  filter(species == "Cod") %>%
  filter(pred_length_cm < 25) %>% 
  group_by(year, quarter, ices_rect, prey_group) %>%
  summarise(tot_prey_weight = sum(tot_prey_weight)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  group_by(year, quarter, ices_rect) %>%
  mutate(cod_prey_prop = tot_prey_weight / sum(tot_prey_weight)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(id = paste(year, quarter, ices_rect, prey_group, sep = "_"))
#> filter: removed 38,685 rows (44%), 49,650 rows remaining
#> filter: removed 33,960 rows (68%), 15,690 rows remaining
#> group_by: 4 grouping variables (year, quarter, ices_rect, prey_group)
#> summarise: now 945 rows and 5 columns, 3 group variables remaining (year, quarter, ices_rect)
#> ungroup: no grouping variables
#> group_by: 3 grouping variables (year, quarter, ices_rect)
#> mutate (grouped): new variable 'cod_prey_prop' (double) with 265 unique values and 8% NA
#> ungroup: no grouping variables
#> mutate: new variable 'id' (character) with 945 unique values and 0% NA

wide_fle <- stom %>% 
  filter(species == "Flounder") %>% 
  group_by(year, quarter, ices_rect, prey_group) %>%
  summarise(tot_prey_weight = sum(tot_prey_weight)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  group_by(year, quarter, ices_rect) %>%
  mutate(fle_prey_prop = tot_prey_weight / sum(tot_prey_weight)) %>%
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(id = paste(year, quarter, ices_rect, prey_group, sep = "_")) %>% 
  dplyr::select(id, fle_prey_prop)
#> filter: removed 49,650 rows (56%), 38,685 rows remaining
#> group_by: 4 grouping variables (year, quarter, ices_rect, prey_group)
#> summarise: now 1,005 rows and 5 columns, 3 group variables remaining (year, quarter, ices_rect)
#> ungroup: no grouping variables
#> group_by: 3 grouping variables (year, quarter, ices_rect)
#> mutate (grouped): new variable 'fle_prey_prop' (double) with 386 unique values and 3% NA
#> ungroup: no grouping variables
#> mutate: new variable 'id' (character) with 1,005 unique values and 0% NA
  
wide <- left_join(wide_cod, wide_fle, by = "id") %>% as.data.frame()
#> left_join: added one column (fle_prey_prop)
#>            > rows only in x   165
#>            > rows only in y  (225)
#>            > matched rows     780
#>            >                 =====
#>            > rows total       945

hist(wide_cod$cod_prey_prop)

hist(wide_fle$fle_prey_prop)


# Calculate Schoener index
schoener <- wide %>% 
  group_by(year, quarter, ices_rect) %>%
  summarise(schoener = 1 - 0.5*(sum(abs(fle_prey_prop - cod_prey_prop)))) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  drop_na(schoener) %>% 
  mutate(id = paste(year, quarter, ices_rect, sep = "_"))
#> group_by: 3 grouping variables (year, quarter, ices_rect)
#> summarise: now 63 rows and 4 columns, 2 group variables remaining (year, quarter)
#> ungroup: no grouping variables
#> drop_na: removed 17 rows (27%), 46 rows remaining
#> mutate: new variable 'id' (character) with 46 unique values and 0% NA

schoener

# Add back in information from the stomach data
stom_sum <- stom %>% 
  group_by(year, quarter, ices_rect) %>% 
  summarise(median_cod_density = median(lcod_kg_km2 + scod_kg_km2),
            median_fle_density = median(fle_kg_km2), 
            median_density = median(lcod_kg_km2 + scod_kg_km2 + fle_kg_km2)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(id = paste(year, quarter, ices_rect, sep = "_")) %>% 
  dplyr::select(id, median_cod_density, median_fle_density, median_density)
#> group_by: 3 grouping variables (year, quarter, ices_rect)
#> summarise: now 82 rows and 6 columns, 2 group variables remaining (year, quarter)
#> ungroup: no grouping variables
#> mutate: new variable 'id' (character) with 82 unique values and 0% NA

schoener <- left_join(schoener, stom_sum, by = "id")
#> left_join: added 3 columns (median_cod_density, median_fle_density, median_density)
#>            > rows only in x    0
#>            > rows only in y  (36)
#>            > matched rows     46
#>            >                 ====
#>            > rows total       46

# Add in X and Y
schoener <- schoener %>% 
  mutate(lat = ices.rect(ices_rect)$lat,
         lon = ices.rect(ices_rect)$lon,
         X = LongLatToUTM(lon, lat, zone = 33)$X / 1000,
         Y = LongLatToUTM(lon, lat, zone = 33)$Y / 1000)
#> mutate: new variable 'lat' (double) with 7 unique values and 0% NA
#>         new variable 'lon' (double) with 6 unique values and 0% NA
#>         new variable 'X' (double) with 16 unique values and 0% NA
